# Peresvet Security Rules

Apply these rules when changing:

- auth
- LDAP
- nginx
- Docker/env configuration
- external input handling
- methods or dynamic execution
- JSONata/expression evaluation
- API handlers
- connectors
- object/tag access behavior

Rules:

- Never commit secrets.
- Do not log passwords, tokens, cookies, credentials or sensitive env values.
- Validate external input.
- Check authorization, not only authentication.
- Avoid exposing internal services through nginx unintentionally.
- Be careful with Docker mounts and host paths.
- Treat dynamic method execution and expression evaluation as high-risk areas.
- Avoid leaking internal stack traces or infrastructure details to users.